Well, the initial commit seemed to work. This is an edit!

OK, here's a summary because I'll never remember!

git config --global user.name "jradxl"
git config --global user.email "<whatever>"
git init johntest1
cd johntest1
git add README
git add sample.c
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/jradxl/johntest1.git
git push origin master

Editing an existing file:
pluma README
git add README
git commit -m "some comment"

So far so good!

Credentials Cache
See https://help.github.com/articles/caching-your-github-password-in-git/
git config --global credential.helper cache




